{
  "page": "Battle of Lann's Point",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <b>Battle of Lann's Point</b> was a battle in which <a href=\"/index.php/House_Lannister\" title=\"House Lannister\">House Lannister</a> fought <a href=\"/index.php/Ironborn\" title=\"Ironborn\">ironborn</a> at <a href=\"/index.php/Lann%27s_Point\" title=\"Lann&#39;s Point\">Lann's Point</a>. <a href=\"/index.php/Lancel_IV_Lannister\" title=\"Lancel IV Lannister\">Lancel IV Lannister</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/King_of_the_Rock\" title=\"King of the Rock\">King of the Rock</a>, is said to have beheaded King <a href=\"/index.php/Harrald_Halfdrowned\" title=\"Harrald Halfdrowned\">Harrald Halfdrowned</a>, as well as Harrald's heir, with a single stroke of his <a href=\"/index.php/Valyrian_steel\" title=\"Valyrian steel\">Valyrian steel</a> sword, <a href=\"/index.php/Brightroar\" title=\"Brightroar\">Brightroar</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf_the_westerlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf_the_westerlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> (however, it was probably a common steel sword of the same name, which has been conflated with the Valyrian blade).<sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;N 1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes\">Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Battle_of_Lann%27s_Point&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Notes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/index.php/Lancel_IV_Lannister\" title=\"Lancel IV Lannister\">Lancel IV Lannister</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Gyles_III_Gardener\" title=\"Gyles III Gardener\">Gyles III Gardener</a> were contemporaries.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rawoiafwilbert_osgrey.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rawoiafwilbert_osgrey.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> As stated by Maester <a href=\"/index.php/Yandel\" title=\"Yandel\">Yandel</a>, they participated in a war involving two kings from the <a href=\"/index.php/Riverlands\" title=\"Riverlands\">riverlands</a> and three from <a href=\"/index.php/Dorne\" title=\"Dorne\">Dorne</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reach:_andals_in_the_reach.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_reach:_andals_in_the_reach.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> indicating an era prior to the riverlands being ruled by <a href=\"/index.php/House_Durrandon\" title=\"House Durrandon\">House Durrandon</a> and Dorne being ruled by <a href=\"/index.php/House_Martell\" title=\"House Martell\">House Martell</a> (centuries before <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon%27s_Conquest\" title=\"Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">Aegon's Conquest</a>). Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Eustace_Osgrey\" title=\"Eustace Osgrey\">Eustace Osgrey</a> says that Lancel IV or <a href=\"/index.php/Lancel_V_Lannister\" title=\"Lancel V Lannister\">Lancel V</a> wielded a <a href=\"/index.php/Valyrian_steel\" title=\"Valyrian steel\">Valyrian steel</a> sword,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> and Yandel writes that Lancel IV wielded the Valyrian steel sword Brightroar and that <a href=\"/index.php/House_Lannister\" title=\"House Lannister\">House Lannister</a> had acquired the blade in the century before the <a href=\"/index.php/Doom_of_Valyria\" title=\"Doom of Valyria\">Doom of Valyria</a> (which occurred a century before the Conquest).<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> According to Elio García, before the Valyrian version of it, the Lannisters had probably wielded other swords named Brightroar, made instead of common steel, and the stories of their actions became merged with the last one (like with <a href=\"/index.php/Ice\" title=\"Ice\">Ice</a> or <a href=\"/index.php/Lady_Forlorn\" title=\"Lady Forlorn\">Lady Forlorn</a>).<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Battle_of_Lann%27s_Point&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiaf_the_westerlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf_the_westerlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Westerlands.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">2.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\">2.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Sworn_Sword\" title=\"The Sworn Sword\">The Sworn Sword</a></i>.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rawoiafwilbert_osgrey.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rawoiafwilbert_osgrey.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_World_of_Ice_and_Fire\" title=\"A World of Ice and Fire\">George R. R. Martin's A World of Ice and Fire</a></i>, Wilbert Osgrey.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_reach:_andals_in_the_reach.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reach:_andals_in_the_reach.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Reach: Andals in the Reach.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Westerlands.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">asoiaf.westeros.org: The ASOIAF wiki thread <a class=\"external text\" href=\"https://asoiaf.westeros.org/index.php?/topic/34958-the-asoiaf-wiki-thread/page/186/#comment-9169389\">Comment by Ran (Novembe